<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Qualia&amp;action=edit&amp;section=30" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<table class="metadata plainlinks mbox-small" style="border:1px solid #aaa; background-color:#f9f9f9;">
<tr>
<td class="mbox-image"><a href="http://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Special:Search/Qualia" title="b:Special:Search/Qualia"><img alt="Sister project" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/df/Wikibooks-logo-en-noslogan.svg/40px-Wikibooks-logo-en-noslogan.svg.png" width="40" height="40" border="0" /></a></td>
<td class="mbox-text" style=""><a href="/wiki/Wikibooks" title="Wikibooks">Wikibooks</a> has a book on the topic of
<div style="margin-left:10px;"><i><b><a href="http://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Consciousness_Studies" class="extiw" title="wikibooks:Consciousness Studies">Consciousness Studies</a></b></i></div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<ul>
<li>Allix, Louis (2004) <i>Perception et réalité: essai sur la nature du visible</i>. Paris: CNRS Éditions.</li>
<li>Alter, Torin, and Walter, Sven (eds.) (2007) <i>Phenomenal Concepts and Phenomenal Knowledge: New Essays on Consciousness and Physicalism</i>. New York and Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/D._M._Armstrong" title="D. M. Armstrong" class="mw-redirect">Armstrong, D. M.</a> (1961) <i>Perception and the Physical World</i>. London: Routledge and Kegan Paul.</li>
<li>Austin, J. L. (1962) <i>Sense and Sensibilia</i>. Oxford; Oxford University Press.</li>
<li>Baker, M. J. (1979) <i>Perceiving, Explaining and Acting</i>. New York: Vantage Press.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Ned_Block" title="Ned Block">Block, Ned</a> (1980) “Are absent qualia possible?” <i>Philosophical Review</i>, 89:2, 257-74.</li>
<li>Block, Ned (1995) “Mental paint”, in <i>Reflections and Replies: Essays on the Philosophy of Tyler Burge</i>, Martin Hahn and Bjørn Ramberg. Cambridge MA: MIT Press. See also <a href="http://www.nyu.edu/gsas/dept/philo/faculty/block/papers/mentalpaint.pdf/" class="external free" title="http://www.nyu.edu/gsas/dept/philo/faculty/block/papers/mentalpaint.pdf/" rel="nofollow">http://www.nyu.edu/gsas/dept/philo/faculty/block/papers/mentalpaint.pdf/</a></li>
<li>Brewer, Bill (1999) <i>Perception and Reason</i>. Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/C._D._Broad" title="C. D. Broad">Broad, C. D.</a> (1923) <i>The Mind and its Place in Nature</i>. London: Kegan Paul, Trench and Trubner.</li>
<li>Brown, Harold (1987) <i>Observation and Objectivity</i>. New York: Oxford University Press.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Peter_Carruthers" title="Peter Carruthers">Carruthers, Peter</a> (2000) <i>Phenomenal Consciousness: a Naturalistic Theory</i>. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press.</li>
<li>Chalmers, David (1996) <i>The Conscious Mind</i>. Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/David_Chalmers" title="David Chalmers">Chalmers, David</a> (ed.). (2002) <i>Philosophy of Mind: Classical and Contemporary Readings</i>, Oxford University Press.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Paul_Churchland" title="Paul Churchland">Churchland, Paul</a>. (1992) "Knowing Qualia: A Reply to Jackson", Chapter 4 in <i>A Neurocomputational Perspective</i>, MIT Press, pp. 67–76. Reprinted in <i>The Nature of Consciousness</i>, 1997, edited by Ned Block, Owen Flanagan, and Guven Guzeldere.</li>
<li>Clark, Austen (1993) <i>Sensory Qualities</i>. Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Jonathan_Dancy" title="Jonathan Dancy">Dancy, Jonathan</a> (1988) <i>Perceptual Knowledge</i>. Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Daniel_Dennett" title="Daniel Dennett">Dennett, D. C.</a> (1988) "Quining qualia", in <i>Consciousness in Contemporary Science</i>, edited by A. Marcel &amp; E. Bisiach, Oxford University Press. <a href="http://ase.tufts.edu/cogstud/papers/quinqual.htm" class="external text" title="http://ase.tufts.edu/cogstud/papers/quinqual.htm" rel="nofollow">Online text</a></li>
<li>Dennett, D. C. (1991) <i><a href="/wiki/Consciousness_Explained" title="Consciousness Explained">Consciousness Explained</a></i>. Little, Brown, and Company.</li>
<li>Dennett, D. C. (1996) "Facing Backwards on the Problem of Consciousness", <i>Journal of Consciousness Studies</i>, vol. 3, no. 1, pp. 4–6. <a href="http://ase.tufts.edu/cogstud/papers/chalmers.htm" class="external text" title="http://ase.tufts.edu/cogstud/papers/chalmers.htm" rel="nofollow">Online text</a></li>
<li>Dennett, D. C. (1998) "The Unimagined Preposterousness of Zombies", in <i>Brainchildren: Essays on Designing Minds</i>, MIT Press and Penguin. <a href="http://ase.tufts.edu/cogstud/papers/unzombie.htm" class="external text" title="http://ase.tufts.edu/cogstud/papers/unzombie.htm" rel="nofollow">Online abstract</a></li>
<li>Drake, Durant (1925) <i>Mind and its Place in Nature</i>. New York: Macmillan.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Fred_Dretske" title="Fred Dretske">Dretske Fred I.</a> (1969) <i>Seeing and Knowing</i>. London: Routledge and Kegan Paul.</li>
<li>Dretske, Fred I. (1987) <i>Naturalizing the Mind</i>. Cambridge MA: MIT Press.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Gerald_Edelman" title="Gerald Edelman">Edelman, G.</a> (1990) <i>The Remembered Present: A Biological Theory of Consciousness</i>, Basic Books.</li>
<li>Edelman, G. and Tononi, G. (2000) <i>Consciousness: How Matter becomes Imagination</i>. London: Allen Lane, The Penguin Press.</li>
<li>Farah, Martha J. (2000) <i>The Cognitive Neuroscience of Vision.</i> Oxford: Blackwell.</li>
<li>Foster, J. (2000) <i>The Nature of Perception</i>. Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>
<li>Garnett, A. Campbell (1965) <i>The Perceptual Process</i>. London: George Allen &amp; Unwin.</li>
<li>Gendler, Tamar Szabó, and Hawthorne, John (eds.) (2006) <i>Perceptual Experience</i>. Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>
<li>Gram, Moltke S. (1983) <i>Direct Realism: A Study of Perception</i>. The Hague: Martinus Mijhoff.</li>
<li>Gregory, R. L. (1993) “Hypothesis and illusion: Explorations in perception and science”, in <i>New Representationalisms: Essays in the Philosophy of Perception</i>, Edmond Wright (ed.). Aldershot: Avebury.</li>
<li>Gunther, York H. (ed.) (2003) <i>Essays on Nonconceptual Content</i>. Cambridge MA: MIT Press.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Gilbert_Harman" title="Gilbert Harman">Harman, Gilbert</a>. (1990) "The Intrinsic Quality of Experience", <i>Philosophical Perspectives, 4, Action Theory and Philosophy of Mind</i>, pp. 31–52.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Stevan_Harnad" title="Stevan Harnad">Harnad, Stevan</a>. (2000) "Correlation vs. Causality: How/Why the Mind/Body Problem Is Hard", <i>Journal of Consciousness Studies</i>, vol. 7, no. 4, pp. 54–61. <a href="http://cogprints.org/1617/" class="external text" title="http://cogprints.org/1617/" rel="nofollow">Online text</a></li>
<li>Harrison, J. (1976) “Direct perception and the sense-datum theory”, in <i>Contemporary British Philosophy, 4th Series: Personal Statements</i>. London: George Allen &amp; Unwin.</li>
<li>Heller, Morton (ed.) (2000) <i>Touch ,Representation, and Blindness</i>. Oxford and New York: Oxford University Press.</li>
<li>Hilbert, David R. (1987) <i>Color and Color Perception: A Study in Anthropocentric Realism</i>. Menlo Park CA: Center for the Study of Language and Information.</li>
<li>Hirst, R. J. (1959) <i>The Problems of Perception</i>. London: George Allen and Unwin.</li>
<li>Holman, E. L. (1979) The problem of theory-laden perception, <i>Philosophical Studies</i>, 35, 91-9.</li>
<li>Horgan, T. (1987) "Supervenient Qualia", <i>Philosophical Review</i>, vol. 96, pp. 491–520.</li>
<li>Huemer, Michael (2001) <i>Skepticism and the Veil of Perception</i>. Lanham, Boulder and New York: Rowman and Littlefield Piublishers, Inc.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Frank_Cameron_Jackson" title="Frank Cameron Jackson">Jackson, Frank</a> (1977) <i>Perception: A Representative Theory</i>. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Frank_Cameron_Jackson" title="Frank Cameron Jackson">Jackson, Frank</a>. (1982) "Epiphenomenal Qualia", <i>Philosophical Quarterly</i>, vol. 32, pp. 127–36. <a href="http://members.aol.com/NeoNoetics/Mary.html" class="external text" title="http://members.aol.com/NeoNoetics/Mary.html" rel="nofollow">Online text</a></li>
<li>Jones, O. R. (1972) “After-images”, <i>American Philosophical Quarterly</i>, 9, 150-8.</li>
<li>Kelley, David (1986) <i>The Evidence of the Senses: a Realist Theory of Perception</i>. Baton Rouge and London: Louisiana State University Press.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Robert_Kirk" title="Robert Kirk">Kirk, Robert</a> (1994) <i>Raw Feeling: A Philosophical Account of the Essence of Consciousness</i>. Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>
<li>Kitcher, P. S. (1979) "Phenomenal Qualities", American Philosophical Quarterly, vol. 16, pp. 123–9.</li>
<li>Kosslyn, S. M. (1980) <i>Image and Mind</i>. Cambridge MA: Harvard University Press.</li>
<li>Kosslyn, S. M. (1994) <i>Image and Brain: The Resolution of the Imagery Debate</i>. Cambridge MA: MIT Press.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Saul_Kripke" title="Saul Kripke">Kripke, Saul</a>. (1971) "Identity and Necessity", in <i>Identity and Individuation</i>, edited by M. K. Munitz, New York: New York University Press.</li>
<li>Landesman, C. (1989) <i>Color and Consciousness: An Essay in Metaphysics</i>. Philadelphia: Temple University Press.</li>
<li>Levine, Joseph (2001) <i>Purple Haze: The Puzzle of Consciousness</i>. Oxford and New York: Oxford University Press.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/C._I._Lewis" title="C. I. Lewis" class="mw-redirect">Lewis, C. I.</a> (1929) <i>Mind and the World Order</i>, New York: C. Scribner's Sons.</li>
<li>Lewis, David. (1995) "Should a Materialist Believe in Qualia?" <i>Australasian Journal of Philosophy</i>, vol. 73, pp. 140–44.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Alphonso_Lingis" title="Alphonso Lingis">Lingis, Alphonso</a> (1996) <i>Sensation: Intelligibility in Sensibility</i>. New York: Humanity Books.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Rodolfo_Llinas" title="Rodolfo Llinas" class="mw-redirect">Llinas, Rodolfo</a> (2001) <i>I of the Vortex</i>. Cambridge MA: MIT Press.</li>
<li>Locke, Don (1967) <i>Perception and our Knowledge of the External world</i>. London: George Allen &amp; Unwin.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Michael_Lockwood_(philosopher)" title="Michael Lockwood (philosopher)">Lockwood, Michael</a> (1989) <i>Mind, Brain and the Quantum: The Compound “I”</i>. Oxford: Blackwell.</li>
<li>Ludlow, Peter, Nagasawa, Yujin, and Stoljar, Daniel (eds.) (2004) <i>There’s Something about Mary: Essays on Phenomenal Consciousness and Frank Jackson’s Knowledge Argument</i>. Cambridge MA: MIT Press.</li>
<li>Lycan, William G. (1996) <i>Consciousness and Experience</i>. Cambridge MA: MIT Press.</li>
<li>MacClachlan, D. L. C. (1989) <i>Philosophy of Perception</i>. Englewood Cliffs NJ: Prentice-Hall.</li>
<li>Mandelbaum, M. (1966) <i>Philosophy, Science and Sense Perception: Historical and Critical Studies</i>. Baltimore MD: the Johns Hopkins University Press.</li>
<li>Matson, Wallace I. (1976) <i>Sentience</i>. Berkeley CA: University of California Press.</li>
<li>Mausfield, Rainer, and Heyer, Dieter (2004) <i>Colour Perception: Mind and the Physical World.</i> Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>
<li>Matthen, Mohan (2005) <i>Seeing, Doing and Knowing: A Philosophical Theory of Sense Perception</i>. Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Colin_McGinn" title="Colin McGinn">McGinn, Colin</a> (1983) <i>The Subjective View</i>. Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>
<li>Millar, Alan (1991) <i>Reasons and Experience</i>. Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>
<li>Mundle, C. W. K. (1971) <i>Perception: Facts and Theories</i>. Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Thomas_Nagel" title="Thomas Nagel">Nagel, Thomas</a>. (1979) "What is it Like to be a Bat?" <i>Mortal Questions</i>, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, pp. 165–180.</li>
<li>Noë, Alva (2005) <i>Action in Perception</i>. Cambridge MA: MIT Press.</li>
<li>Noë, Alva and Thompson, Evan (eds.) (2002) <i>Vision and Mind: Selected Readings in the Philosophy of Perception</i>. Cambridge MA: MIT Press.</li>
<li>Palmer, Stephen E. (2002) <i>Vision Science: Photons to Phenomenology.</i> Cambridge MA: MIT Press.</li>
<li>Peacocke, C. (1983) <i>Sense and Content: Experience, Thought and their Relations</i>. Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>
<li>Pennycuick, J. (1971) <i>In Contact with the Physical World</i>. London: George Allen &amp; Unwin.</li>
<li>Pharoah, M. C. (online). <a href="http://homepage.ntlworld.com/m.pharoah/" class="external text" title="http://homepage.ntlworld.com/m.pharoah/" rel="nofollow">Looking to systems theory for a reductive explanation of phenomenal experience and evolutionary foundations for higher order thought</a> Retrieved Dec.14 2007.</li>
<li>Pitcher G. (1971) <i>A Theory of Perception</i>. Princeton NJ: Princeton University Press.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/H._H._Price" title="H. H. Price">Price, H. H.</a> (1932) <i>Perception</i>. London: Methuen.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/V._S._Ramachandran" title="V. S. Ramachandran" class="mw-redirect">Ramachandran, V. S.</a> and Blakeslee, Sandra (1999) <i>Phantoms in the Brain: Human Nature and the Architecture of Mind</i>. London: Fourth Estate.</li>
<li>Richardson, John T. E. (1999) <i>Imagery</i>. Hove: Psychology Press Ltd.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/David_M._Rosenthal" title="David M. Rosenthal">Rosenthal, David M.</a> (2005) <i>Consciousness and Mind</i>. Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>
<li>Ross, Jacob J. (1970) <i>The Appeal to the Given: A Study in Epistemology</i>. London: George Allen &amp; Unwin.</li>
<li>Rundle, Bede (1972) <i>Perception, Sensation and Verification</i>. Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>
<li>Schwartz, Robert (1994) <i>Vision: Variations on Some Berkleian Themes</i>. Oxford: Blackwell.</li>
<li>Schwartz, Robert (ed.) (2004) <i>Perception</i>. Oxford: Blackwell.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/John_Searle" title="John Searle">Searle, John</a>. (1997) <i>The Mystery of Consciousness</i>, New York: New York Review Books.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Roy_Wood_Sellars" title="Roy Wood Sellars">Sellars , Roy Wood</a> (1932) <i>The Philosophy of Physical Realism</i>. New York: Macmillan.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Wilfrid_Sellars" title="Wilfrid Sellars">Sellars, Wilfrid</a> (1981) <i>The Carus Lectures</i>, The Monist, 64, 3-90.</li>
<li>Smith, A. D. (2002) <i>The Problem of Perception</i>. Cambridge MA: Harvard University Press.</li>
<li>Smith, Quentin, and Jokic, Aleksandar (eds.) <i>Consciousness: New Philosophical Perspectives</i>. Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>
<li>Soltis, J. F. (1966) <i>Seeing, Knowing and Believing: A Study of the Language of Visual Perception</i>. London: George Allen and Unwin.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Barry_Stroud" title="Barry Stroud">Stroud, Barry</a> (2000) <i>The Quest for Reality: Subjectivism and the Metaphysics of Colour</i>. New York and Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>
<li>Thau, Michael (2002) <i>Consciousness and Cognition</i>. Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>
<li>Thompson, Evan 1995) <i>Colour Vision: A Study in Cognitive Science and the Philosophy of Perception.</i> London and New York: Routledge.</li>
<li>Valberg, J. J. (1992) <i>The Puzzle of Experience</i>. Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>
<li>Vision, Gerald (1997) <i>Problems of Vision: Rethinking the Causal Theory of Perception</i>. New York and London: Oxford University Press.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/G._J._Warnock" title="G. J. Warnock" class="mw-redirect">Warnock, G. J.</a> (!955-6) “Seeing”, <i>Proceedings of the Aristotelian Society</i>, 55, 201-18.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/G._J._Warnock" title="G. J. Warnock" class="mw-redirect">Warnock, G. J.</a> (ed.) (1967) <i>The Philosophy of Perception</i>. Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>
<li>Westphal, Jonathan (1987) <i>Colour: Some Philosophical Problems from Wittgenstein</i>. Oxford: Blackwell.</li>
<li>Wright, Edmond (1989) Querying “Quining Qualia”, <i>Acta Analytica</i>, 4, 9-31.</li>
<li>Wright, Edmond (2008) <a href="http://mitpress.mit.edu/catalog/item/default.asp?ttype=2&amp;tid=11485" class="external text" title="http://mitpress.mit.edu/catalog/item/default.asp?ttype=2&amp;tid=11485" rel="nofollow"><i>The Case for Qualia</i>, MIT Press, Cambridge, MA</a></li>
<li>Wright, Edmond (2005) <a href="http://www.palgrave.com/products/title.aspx?is=1403990670" class="external text" title="http://www.palgrave.com/products/title.aspx?is=1403990670" rel="nofollow"><i>Narrative, Perception, Language, and Faith</i>, Palgrave-Macmillan, Basingstoke</a></li>
</ul>
